{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Flair features several pretrained language models, embeddings and functions to stack different language representations.We stacked the medical fastText embeddings (the same employed with SequenceLabeler) and the contextual string embeddings provided in Flair; these are general embeddings pre-trained using the Spanish Wikipedia.",
    "We applied almost the same hyperparameters as in [66]: stochastic gradient descent optimizer, hidden states per layer = 256, dropout = 0.5, and batch size = 32.",
    "Likewise, the learning rate was initialized to 0.1, and halved if training loss did not improved for 5 epochs.",
    "The maximum number of epochs was set to 100 (although our experiments stopped training before that limit).",
    "We provide a Python notebook for replicating the experiment."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We applied almost the same hyperparameters as in [66]: stochastic gradient descent optimizer, hidden states per layer = 256, dropout = 0.5, and batch size = 32."
  ]
}